The Degree in Biotechnology allows:
registration in Section B of the Register (Junior Biotechnologist) of the National Association of Italian Biotechnologists, registration in the Order of Biologists (Junior Register) and in the Order of Agronomists and Forestry Doctors, after passing the state exam and acquisition of the qualification;
the possibility of continuing studies in various classes of Master's Degrees or first-level Masters.
Graduates will be able to find employment as:
Scientific drug representative: figure who is responsible for providing technical information to general practitioners and specialists regarding the pharmacological lines of the reference company.
Scientific Area Specialist: figure who is responsible for providing scientific information only on certain lines of drugs (for example: oncology drugs) of which they have in-depth knowledge of the molecular aspects,
Laboratory technician: the three-year graduate can work as a technician in analysis laboratories in the agri-food, environmental, research and pharmaceutical industry sectors.
Employee of a parapharmacy or owner of a parapharmacy: a biotechnologist can be the owner of a parapharmacy (as it concerns ownership) or work as an employee but always in the presence of a qualified and registered pharmacist.
Graduates will be able to find employment in:
Universities and public and private research institutions;
National and Private Health Service Facilities;
Biotechnological Industries and Services; Drug industry and supervision;
Dietetic-food industry;
Environmental Prevention Bodies;
Multi-zonal prevention measures, PMP;
Medical-legal structures;
Diagnostic and Pharmaceutical Industry;
Biotech industry;
Notified and certification bodies;
National and international regulatory agencies;
Clinical trial monitoring (CRA or Clinical Monitor, CM);
Patent offices;
Technology transfer company;
Scientific publishing and communication company;
Management consulting and/or savings management company (Venture Capital);
Charities;
